!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

yard /jɑːd/

(yards) 

1. N-COUNT A yard is a unit of length equal to thirty-six inches or approximately 91.4 centimetres. 码 

例： The incident took place about 500 yards from where he was standing. 该事件发生在距他所站位置约五百码处。 

例： ...a long narrow strip of linen two or three yards long. …一条两三码长的细长亚麻布条。 

2. N-COUNT A yard is a flat area of concrete or stone that is next to a building and often has a wall around it. 院子 

例： I saw him standing in the yard. 我看见他站在院子里。 

3. N-COUNT You can refer to a large open area where a particular type of work is done as a yard . (进行某种作业的) 场地 

例： ...a rail yard. …一个铁路调车场。 

4. N-COUNT A yard is a piece of land next to someone's house, with grass and plants growing in it. 庭院 [美国英语] 

例： He dug a hole in our yard on Edgerton Avenue to plant a maple tree when I was born. 他在我出生时在埃杰顿大道我家的院子里挖了个坑，种了一棵枫树。

</div>

